    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-01-17T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-01-17T13:00:00-05:00" n="359"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d359">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">033.3211 Aranha, Oswaldo/10: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Scotten</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-01-17T15:00:00-03:00"
                            >January 17, 1939—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 17—2:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>16. For the Under Secretary. Your 12, January 16, 8 p.m. Aranha is highly pleased
                    with the suggested agenda which he feels covers all matters to be discussed with
                    the exception of immigration. He <pb facs="0359" n="351" xml:id="pg_351"/>
                    explained that the question of Japanese and other immigration into Brazil is a
                    subject of mutual interest and he desires during the discussions to ascertain
                    our views …</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>He is planning to proceed on the <hi rend="italic">Nieuw Amsterdam</hi> and his
                    present plans are to take with him Joao Carlos Muniz, the chief of his Cabinet,
                    and Sergio lima E. Silva, a diplomatic secretary, who is a member of his
                    staff.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Scotten</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
